  "response_text": "Against a black background, a mound of white telephone receivers is stacked across the bottom of the screen. The handsets lie in different directions, their rounded earpieces and mouthpieces overlapping like a pile of identical telephone parts. Behind the heap, a small, rounded black-and-white “GTE” logo begins to appear, centered above the receivers. As the pile seems to drop lower in the picture or the logo becomes more prominent, the letters “GTE” stand out in bold white block type inside a rounded black rectangle, with a soft reflected shadow beneath it.\n\nThe telephone receivers give way to a darker product-display setting. The GTE logo sits in the center, low against a black background, while two tall rectangular speaker cabinets stand on either side, angled slightly inward. Each speaker has a pale wood-toned frame and a dark, patterned grille, suggesting home stereo equipment. The central GTE logo grows larger between them until the letters dominate the middle of the screen.\n\nThe imagery shifts to lighting. The GTE logo remains centered on a dark stage-like surface, and several glowing light bulbs hang above it in a row. The bulbs vary slightly in shape and size, from rounded household-style bulbs to smaller narrow bulbs, all shining white. A later image shows the logo beneath a larger display of round lamp faces arranged in neat rows, like a grid of spotlights or bulbs. The circular lights brighten until they nearly wash the screen in white.\n\nThe commercial then turns into more abstract electronic and lighting patterns. Rows of colored shapes appear against black: red-orange rectangular squares in a grid across the top and middle, with a row of yellow-orange glowing circles along the bottom. Some of the red squares are paler pink or white, as if individual indicator lights are turning on among the darker red ones. The arrangement resembles an illuminated control panel or communications display.\n\nNear the end, the background becomes pale and nearly white. A single small “GTE” logo appears in black at the center. A second logo appears below and slightly to the right, and then many tiny “GTE” logos begin multiplying across the screen. They accumulate in rows and columns, forming larger shapes. The repeated miniature logos build into the outlines of enormous block letters. First partial strokes and corners appear, then the shapes become recognizable as a large “GTE” wordmark. By the final image, the full GTE logo fills most of the screen: a thick rounded rectangular border containing the large letters “GTE,” all constructed from hundreds of tiny repeated “GTE” marks.",
